    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="630" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                <head>No. 68.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Manning</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 31, 1887</date>. (Received September
                                        14.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 204.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your circular, dated
                                    July 9, 1887, suggesting the abolition of tonnage duties and
                                    equivalent charges on navigation, I have to report that the same
                                    was forwarded to Mr. Mariscal, and he has replied that he has
                                    sent the circular to the treasury department, requesting
                                    information on the subject.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Th. C.
                                    Manning.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
